-- Chrysler says December U.S. sales fall 53 percent
-- 
-- Mon Jan 5, 2009 3:21pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/01/05/us-chrysler-sales-sb-idUSTRE5044O820090105

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - Chrysler says U.S. sales fall 53 percent in December from year earlier. 

 * Chrysler says US sales fell 30 percent in 2008 from prior year * Chrysler says offering additional discounts of up to $1,000 when customers finance through local credit unions in 2009 * Chrysler says finished December with inventory of 397,569 vehicles, down 9 percent from a year earlier * Chrysler says end December inventory equaled 115-day supply of sales (Reporting by  David Bailey )